				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\:\tau\:$$\end{document}, (ii) Smoothing window duration, (iii) Dilation radius, (iv) Maximum merge gap, (v) Minimum overlap with ground-truth events to count a detection, and (vi) Minimum predicted event duration. For each parameter combination, we compute event-level metrics on Dev. We enforced a minimum window-level specificity (specificity ≥ 0.93). An upper bound on false alarms per hour, based on a predefined value (FA/h ≤ 0.69). Among configurations that satisfy these constraints, we selected the one that maximizes event sensitivity, with secondary tie-breaking based on time-based recall and positive predictive value. The selected parameters and threshold are then frozen and applied to the Eval split, where we compute the final window- and event-level metrics.

